litary%20Commission%20CMC%2C%20extends%20Spring%20Festival%20greetings%20to%20the%20country's%20military%20veterans%20when%20attending%20a%20gala%20held%20by%20the%20CMC%20for%20retired%20military%20officers%20of%20Beijing-based%20troops%20in%20Beijing%2C%20capital%20of%20China%2C%20Jan.%2029%2C%202024.%3Cp%3ELi%20Gang%2FXinhua%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Pentagon's%20report%20on%20China's%20military%20makes%20Beijing%20seem%20weaker%20than%20it%20is%2C%20two%20analysts%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%202023%20report%20said%20China's%20defense%20budget%20is%20about%20%24230%20billion%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20US'%20%24889%20billion.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20researchers%20said%20this%20left%20out%20key%20factors%20such%20as%20research%20budgets%20or%20China's%20spending%20power.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBeijing's%20military%20spending%20and%20threat%20are%20likely%20far%20higher%20than%20portrayed%20by%20the%20Pentagon%2C%20which%20recently%20reported%20figures%20that%20indicate%20China's%20defense%20budget%20was%20nearly%20four%20times%20smaller%20than%20America's%2C%20two%20US%20analysts%20said%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.defense.gov%2F2023%2FOct%2F19%2F2003323409%2F-1%2F-1%2F1%2F2023-MILITARY-AND-SECURITY-DEVELOPMENTS-INVOLVING-THE-PEOPLES-REPUBLIC-OF-CHINA.PDF%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannual%20report%20to%20Congress%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20published%20in%20October%202023%2C%20covered%20military%20developments%20in%20China%20in%202022%20and%20reported%20that%20Beijing%20spent%20%24230%20billion%20that%20year%20on%20defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20that%20spending%20was%20put%20toward%20strengthening%20its%20ability%20to%20take%20Taiwan%20by%20force%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20with%20aggressive%20expansions%20to%20its%20navy%2C%20air%20force%2C%20and%20nuclear%20arsenal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Congress%20in%20December%20