2_blank%5C%22%3Erequested%20%24145%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20research%2C%20development%2C%20and%20testing%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20also%20operates%20a%20%26quot%3Bcivil-military%20fusion%26quot%3B%20strategy%2C%20which%20allows%20its%20military%20to%20access%20intellectual%20property%20and%20technology%20from%20its%20civilian%20sectors%20freely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConfusingly%2C%20the%20report%20does%20not%20attempt%20to%20account%20for%20either%20of%20these%20significant%20considerations%20in%20its%20treatment%20of%20China's%20defense%20budget%20topline%2C%26quot%3B%20Peters%20and%20Beaver%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EChina%20can%20pay%20its%20soldiers%20a%20lot%20less%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20China's%20higher%20spending%20power%20means%20a%20smaller%20budget%20can%20go%20a%20lot%20further%2C%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%2C%20Beijing%20pays%20its%20soldiers%20a%20lot%20less%20than%20the%20US%20does%2C%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%20Chinese%20recruits%20earn%20a%20reported%20%24108%20per%20month%2C%20per%20an%20oft-cited%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fgraphic-detail%2F2021%2F05%2F01%2Fnominal-spending-figures-understate-chinas-military-might%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Economist%20in%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%2016%20times%20lower%20than%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-military-service-members-make-2019-2%23e-1-20340-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%241%2C900%20salary%20for%20US%20recruits.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeters%20and%20Beaver%20estimated%20that%20in%20general%2C%20%26quot%3BChinese%20military%20personnel%20earn%20only%20about%20one-fourth%20what%20American%20servicemembers%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSimply%20put%2C%20defense%20spending%20goes%20a%20lot%20further%20in%20China%20than%20it%20does%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20because%20labor%20and%20material%20costs%20are%20lower%20in%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20true%20military%20spending%20has%20drawn%20renewed%20attention%20after%20Sen.%20Dan%20Sullivan%20of%20Alaska%20said%20in%20September%20that%20internal%20US%20assessments%20indicate%20Beijing's%20annual%20defense%20budget%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2023%2F09%2F19%2Fchina-defense-budget-military-weapons-purchasing-power%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24700%20billion%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecompared%20to%20Beijing's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fenglish.scio.gov.cn%2Fchinavoices%2F2023-03%2F06%2Fcontent_85146919.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%20%24224%20billion%20for%202023.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Stavridis%2C%20former%20supreme%20allied%20commander%20for%20the%20National%20Atlantic%20Treaty%20Organization%2C%20said%20in%20September%20that%20if%20China's%20budget%20was%20truly%20%24700%20billion%2C%20it%20is%20growing%20quickly%20and%20would%20account%20for%20around%204%25%20of%20the%20country's%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20trajectory%20alone%20is%20concerning%2C%26quot%3B%20Stavridis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fopinion%2Farticles%2F2023-09-13%2Fchina-spends-700-billion-on-its-military-approaching-us-900-billion%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20for%20Bloomberg.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stats.gov.cn%2Fsj%2Fzxfb%2F202401%2Ft20240117_1946624.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20GDP%20for%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20around%20%2417.8%20trillion.%20The%20US%20spends%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.worldbank.org%2Findicator%2FMS.MIL.XPND.GD.ZS%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3.5%25%20of%20its%20GDP%20on%20its%20military%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20should%20avoid%20overreacting%20to%20what%20seems%20to%20be%20this%20more%20accurate%20data%20of%20China's%20military%20push%2C%26quot%3B%20Stavridis%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20the%20first%20step%20is%20for%20the%20Pentagon%20to%20talk%20about%20it%2C%20and%20not%20just%20in%20Washington's%20halls%20of%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeters%20and%20Beaver%20urged%20the%20same%2C%20warning%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bmassive%20disconnect%20between%20the%20US%20government's%20sense%20of%20the%20threat%20posed%20by%20China's%20military%20spending%20and%20the%20public%20perception%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20as%20worrying%20as%20this%20report%20is%2C%20it%20almost%20certainly%20underestimates%20the%20threat%20posed%20by%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon's%20press%20office%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-defense-budget-china-undersells-true-military-strength-analysts-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706763728000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bb175f7a3d271488766ffe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-defense-budget-china-undersells-true-military-strength-analysts-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%202023%20assessment%20didn't%20account%20for%20military%20research%20spending%2C%20or%20consider%20how%20China%20pays%20its%20soldiers%20far%20less%20than%20the%20US%2C%20the%20researchers%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-defense-budget-china-undersells-true-military-strength-analysts-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Acchoot%20Doesn%E2%80%99t%20Mean%20Dalit%2C%20Congress%20Politicises%2