njana%2C%20the%20immaculate%20one%20who%20had%20previously%20come%20down%20to%20Earth%20as%20the%20Hindu%20deity%20Rama.%20By%20the%20time%20of%20Akbar%20you%20have%20a%20widespread%20belief%20among%20the%20Muslims%20of%20Braj%20that%20Krishna%20is%20a%20prophet%20of%20Islam%2C%20and%20by%20the%20time%20of%20Shah%20Jahan%20you%20have%20Dara%20Shikoh%20writing%20of%20the%20Vedic%20origins%20of%20Quran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20syncretic%20thought%20always%20coexisted%20with%20a%20more%20hardline%20sense%20of%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMughal%20India%20was%20not%20a%20time%20of%20communal%20bliss%2C%20and%20there%20are%20numerous%20communal%20riots%20throughout%20the%20period.%20Emperors%20like%20Aurangzeb%20very%20actively%20alienated%20the%20Rajput%20alliance%20that%20Akbar%20spent%20so%20long%20building%20up.%20And%20whilst%20temple%20construction%20reach%20unprecedented%20levels%20under%20Akbar%20and%20Jahangir%2C%20including%20the%20imperial%20sponsorship%20of%2037%20temples%20in%20Vrindavan%20and%20Mathura%20alone%2C%20new%20temple%20construction%20virtually%20comes%20to%20a%20halt%20under%20Shah%20Jahan%20and%20Aurangzeb.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20later%20Mughals%2C%20who%20far%20too%20few%20people%20in%20modern%20India%20know%20about%2C%20were%20by%20far%20the%20most%20syncretic%20in%20their%20practices%2C%20celebrating%20Holi%20and%20performing%20in%20Ram%20Leelas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistorians%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20violence%20of%20Partition%2C%20and%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20what%20they%20saw%20as%20nation%20building%2C%20tended%20to%20underplay%20the%20violence%20and%20the%20iconoclasm%20that%20took%20place%20particularly%20in%20the%20Sultanate%20period.%20Today%2C%20of%20course%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20dealing%20with%20the%20other%20extreme%20where%20almost%20all%20that%20anyone%20knows%20about%20Indian%20Islamic%20history%20is%20iconoclasm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20truth%20is%20more%20nuanced%2C%20and%20it%20varies%20from%20place%20to%20place%20and%20time%20to%20time.%20In%20the%20Mughal%20period%20for%20example%2C%20it%20varies%20from%20emperor%20to%20emperor%20%E2%80%93%20what%20is%20true%20of%20Akbar%20is%20not%20true%20of%20Aurangzeb%2C%20and%20vice%20versa%3B%20or%2C%20in%20the%20Sultanate%2C%20what%20is%20true%20of%20Allauddin%20Kilji%20is%20not%20true%20of%20Balban.%20One%20can%E2%80%99t%20just%20take%20a%20broad%20brush%20and%20approach%20saying%20Islamic%20rule%20is%20one%20thing%20for%20a%20thousand%20years.%20You%20have%20to%20look%20in%20detail%20at%20specific%20events%20and%20specific%20rulers.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20complex%20and%20hugely%20varied%20picture%20over%20a%20long%20period%20of%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20there%20an%20Islamic%20orthodoxy%20at%20the%20time%20that%20challenged%20the%20openness%20of%20Islam%20both%20during%20the%20Sultanate%20and%20Mughal%20reign%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20have%20complaints%20as%20early%20as%20the%20reign%20of%20Balban%20from%20conservative%20Islamic%20clerics%20that%20Hindus%20are%20prospering%20in%20Sultanate%20Delhi%2C%20that%20temples%20are%20being%20built%2C%20festivals%20being%20celebrated%20and%20Hindu%20religious%20processions%20are%20filling%20the%20streets.%20That%20many%20of%20the%20Hindus%20are%20far%20richer%20than%20the%20Muslims%20and%20that%20Muslims%20are%20their%20servants.%20The%20Delhi%20Sultanate%20ruled%20300%20years%2C%20from%201206%20to%201500s%20till%20the%20Mughals%20came%2C%20and%20this%20complaint%20came%20as%20early%20as%20the%20reign%20of%20Balban%20in%201266.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sultanate%20is%20a%20long%20period%20and%20unquestionably%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20of%20violence%20and%20iconoclasm%2C%20especially%20at%20the%20beginning%3B%20but%20equally%20you%20find%20that%20Hindus%20are%20doing%20very%20well%20too%20in%20certain%20reigns%20and%20at%20certain%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDid%20religion%20define%20Muslim%20rule%20in%20India%20at%20all%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReligion%20is%20certainly%20important%2C%20and%20there%20is%20evidence%20that%20some%20sultans%20saw%20themselves%20as%20champions%20of%20Islam.%20But%20again%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20complicated.%20Muhammad%20of%20Ghor%2C%20who%20we%20remember%20is%20a%20great%20iconoclast%2C%20actually%20has%20Lakshmi%20on%20the%20back%20of%20his%20coins%20and%20is%20from%20a%20heretical%20fringe%20sect%20that%20many%20Sunnis%20regard%20as%20extremely%20dodgy.%20And%20the%20Mughals%20in%20particular%20seem%20to%20be%20misunderstood%20because%20the%20entire%20Mughal%20war%20machine%20is%20built%20on%20collaboration%20with%20the%20Rajputs%20of%20Rajasthan.%20And%20apart%20from%20the%20inter-marriages%20that%20took%20place%20generation%20after%20generation%20from%20Akbar%20onwards%2C%20some%20of%20the%20greatest%20Mughal%20battles%20are%20led%20by%20Hindu%20generals%20and%20armies%20from%20Rajasthan.%20Some%20of%20the%20most%20hard%20won%20campaigns%20of%20the%20Mughals%20were%20in%20the%20Deccan%20against%20Deccani%20Muslim%20Sultanates%20and%20led%20by%20Rajasthani%20Hindus%20generals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20one%20still%20say%20that%20there%20was%20a%20period%20of%20Islamic%20heritage%20that%20was%20open%2C%20embracing%20of%20other%20cultures%2C%20syncretic%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20colonial%20period%2C%20at%20the%20very%20end%20of%20Mughal%20rule%2C%20when%20you%20have%20a%20Shah%20Alam%20II%20and%20Bahadur%20Shah%20II%20Zafar%20on%20the%20throne%20there%20is%20a%20world%20that%20is%20really%20very%20closely%20integrated.%20There%20was%20the%20Ram%20Leela%20procession%20that%20was%20diverted%20from%20its%20path%20so%20that%20it%20could%20pass%20by%20the%20palace%20at%20the%20request%20of%20Zafar.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20moment%20I%20found%20in%20the%20palace%20diary%20where%20Bahadur%20Shah%20Zafar%20refuses%20to%20give%20permission%20to%20a%20Hindu%20who%20wishes%20to%20convert%20to%20Islam.%20Hindu%20khatris%20attend%20madrassas.%20Sufi%20shrines%20welcome%20all%20religions.%20And%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20Mughal%20Delhi%20are%20the%20Jain%20bankers%20who%20are%20providing%20the%20cash%20and%20are%20the%20engine%20which%20keeps%20the%20whole%20machine%20running.%20It%20is%20a%20thoroughly%20mixed%20world%20in%20the%20city%2C%20everyone%20is%20living%20cheek%20by%20jowl%20in%20a%20way%20that%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20imagine%20in%20the%20post-Partition%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20it%20was%20the%20belief%20of%20the%20ruler%20that%20made%20Islam%20dogmatic%20or%20syncretic%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20generation%20is%20different%3B%20like%20today%2C%20in%20the%20last%2020%20years%20we%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20different%20rulers%2C%20each%20with%20different%20views.%20The%20same%20is%20true%20of%20in%20the%2016th%20century%2C%20there%20are%20rulers%20who%20are%20very%20syncretic%20and%20you%20find%20shared%20festivals%20and%20shared%20shrines%2C%20but%20you%20will%20also%20find%20conservatives%20on%20both%20sides%20who%20won%E2%80%99t%20mix.%20Even%20during%20Akbar%E2%80%99s%20reign%20you%20will%20find%20many%20conservative%20mullahs%20who%20will%20write%20badly%20of%20Hinduism%20and%20vice%20versa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20belies%20the%20complexity%20that%20you%20have%20at%20the%20same%20moment%20in%20the%20same%20family%2C%20Dara%20Shikoh%20who%20is%20busy%20writing%20the%20Mingling%20of%20Two%20Oceans%2C%20and%20seeing%20a%20Vedic%20origin%20for%20the%20Quran%20%E2%80%93%20however%20factually%20untrue%20it%20is%20%E2%80%93%20and%20is%20a%20measure%20of%20the%20Sufi%20thought%20of%20the%20time.%20Meanwhile%20his%20brother%20Aurangzeb%20is%20a%20puritanical%20bigot%20who%20strongly%20disagrees%20with%20all%20of%20this.%20But%20is%20true%20that%20at%20the%20time%20of%20Dara%20Shikoh%20and%20in%20Akbar%E2%80%99s%20time%20there%20existed%20syncretic%20tendencies%2C%20shared%20shrines%20and%20shared%20experiences%20the%20extent%20of%20which%20which%20is%20almost%20unimaginable%20in%20the%20religious%20polarisation%20of%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETemple%20destruction%20was%20also%20rampant%20among%20victorious%20Hindu%20kings%20even%20before%20the%20Muslims%20came%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECorrect%2C%20but%20again%20it%E2%80%99s%20slightly%20different%2C%20in%20that%20the%20local%20deity%20was%20kidnapped%20by%20the%20victorious%20Hindu%20king.%20When%20you%20go%20to%20the%20Tanjore%20Museum%20today%2C%20you%20can%20find%20four%20or%20five%20deities%20which%20were%20taken%20from%20Orissa%20and%20Bengal%20by%20the%20victorious%20Cholas.%20Now%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20hostile%20act%2C%20taking%20away%20the%20source%20of%20your%20enemies%20power%3B%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20quite%20the%20same%20as%20what%20Mohammed%20bin%20Tughlaq%20was%20doing%2C%20which%20is%20burying%20the%20idol%20beneath%20the%20step%20of%20the%20mosque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20we%20look%20at%20the%20present%20day%20hardening%20and%20fundamentalist%20strain%20of%20Islam%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20true%20that%20in%20the%20past%20too%20you%20will%20find%20strains%20of%20Islam%20that%20is%20every%20bit%20as%20hard%20line%20as%20the%20Taliban%20today.%20%E2%80%A6Today%20you%20can%20go%20to%20one%20area%20of%20Delhi%20and%20find%20a%20Sufi%20in%20Nizamuddin%20who%20would%20welcome%20Hindus%20and%20Sikhs%2C%20and%20also%20find%20somewhere%20else%20a%20more%20hardline%20Mullah%20who%20would%20not.%20The%20same%20was%20true%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20Islam%20too%20has%20a%20varied%20spectrum%20of%20belief%20as%20Hinduism%20does%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20widespread%20belief%20today%20in%20India%20that%20Islam%20is%20a%20religion%20that%20encourages%20the%20breaking%20of%20idols%2C%20promotes%20violence%20against%20other%20religions%2C%20whereas%20Hinduism%20is%20a%20religion%20of%20peace%20which%20never%20made%20war%20outside%20India%20and%20which%20didn%E2%80%99t%20break%20the%20temples%20of%20its%20rivals.%20Neither%20of%20these%20broad%20stereotypes%20is%20all%20true%20%E2%80%93%20there%20are%20very%20clear%20examples%20of%20on%20one%20hand%2C%20an%20Islamic%20ruler%20like%20Ibrahim%20Adil%20Shah%20II%20of%20Bijapur%20writing%20hymns%20to%20Saraswati%20and%20other%20Hindu%20Gods%20and%20Goddesses%3B%20or%20of%20the%20Cholas%20looting%20jewels%20and%20destroying%20temples%20in%20Anuradapura%20in%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20for%20example%2C%20and%20the%20Sri%20Lankan%20chronicles%20have%20written%20about%20the%20violence.%20You%20have%20other%20Hindu%20rulers%2C%20from%20the%20Chalukya%20to%20the%20Cholas%20who%20levelled%20whole%20cities%20and%20temples%2C%20and%20carried%20off%20the%20idols%20of%20their%20rivals%20to%20their%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sri%20Lankan%20chronicles%20accuse%20Rajaraja%20Chola%20of%20burning%20down%20temples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20examples%20of%20violent%20men%20breaking%20temples%20on%20both%20sides%2C%20and%20there%20are%20examples%20of%20syncretic%2C%20peaceable%20rulers%20on%20both%20sides%20too.%20The%20trouble%20is%20when%20people%20are%20selective%20in%20their%20reading%20of%20history%2C%20choosing%20items%20from%20history%20to%20illustrate%20their%20politics%2C%20as%20if%20it%E2%80%99s%20an%20a%20la%20carte%20menu%20in%20a%20restaurant%20and%20ignoring%20the%20evidence%20to%20the%20contrary.%20History%20written%20like%20that%20is%20necessarily%20full%20of%20half%20truths.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWould%20you%20say%20Sufism%20brought%20an%20element%20of%20openness%20to%20Islam%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20there%20are%20many%20Sufis%20who%20acted%20to%20bring%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%20together%20but%20you%20also%20have%20warrior%20Sufis%20%E2%80%93%20my%20message%20is%20that%20you%20have%20to%20study%20history%20in%20depth%20and%20in%20detail%20and%20look%20at%20particularities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20is%20true%20is%20that%20there%20are%20moments%20of%20cohabitation%2C%20coexistence%2C%20and%20a%20coalescing%20of%20interest.%20The%20Mughal%20Empire%20was%20built%20with%20Rajput%20help%20and%20Rajput%20armies%20and%20it%20was%20a%20coalition%20of%20self-interest%20that%20brought%20them%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20greatest%20collection%20of%20Deccani%20manuscripts%20today%20is%20to%20be%20found%20in%20Bikaner%2C%20because%20the%20Bikaner%20armies%20led%20the%20Mughal%20army%E2%80%99s%20attacks%20on%20the%20Deccan%20and%20brought%20the%20manuscripts%20back%20as%20loot%20to%20Bikaner.%20And%20why%20did%20they%20join%20with%20the%20Mughals%3F%20Because%20it%20was%20in%20their%20self-interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkbar%E2%80%99s%20achievement%20was%20to%20build%20a%20coalition%20of%20self-interest%20so%20that%20both%20people%20profited%20%E2%80%93%20when%20you%20see%20the%20very%20modest%20scale%20of%20the%20small%20haveli%20of%20the%20early%20Kachawa%20kings%20of%20Amer%20and%20compare%20it%20to%20the%20massive%20scale%20of%20the%20later%20Amer%20Fort%20built%20from%20the%20time%20of%20Akbar%2C%20you%20can%20see%20how%20much%20more%20money%20and%20wealth%20is%20being%20channeled%20into%20those%20Rajasthani%20Hindu%20kingdoms.%20And%20they%20are%20gaining%20by%20a%20coalition%20of%20self-interest%20with%20the%20Mughals.%20Like%20politicians%20today%2C%20rulers%20make%20calculation%20based%20on%20what%20will%20benefit%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20prosperity%20comes%20with%20political%20alliances%2C%20not%20necessarily%20syncretism%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Raja%20Mansingh%20is%20sent%20by%20Akbar%20as%20governor%20of%20Bihar%20and%20you%20find%20two%20very%20different%20inscriptions%20above%20his%20palace%20there%20%E2%80%93%20one%20is%20in%20Persian%20where%20he%20says%20he%20is%20the%20humble%20servant%20of%20Emperor%20Akbar%2C%20the%20other%20is%20in%20Sanskrit%20where%20he%20says%20he%20is%20the%20greatest%20ruler%20who%20bows%20to%20no%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20here%20you%20see%20the%20complexity%20%E2%80%93%20here%E2%80%99s%20a%20man%20who%20is%20making%20a%20deal%20with%20himself%20or%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20his%20people%2C%20and%20Jaipur%20gains%20through%20this%20alliance%20%E2%80%93%20its%20a%20bit%20like%20Nitish%20Kumar%20today.%20Likewise%2C%20the%20Jain%20bankers%20who%20lend%20to%20the%20Mughals%20do%20so%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20good%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20message%20is%20that%20the%20past%20is%20as%20complex%20as%20the%20present.%20And%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20historian%E2%80%99s%20job%20to%20bring%20out%20that%20complexity%20and%20nuance%20and%20to%20push%20back%20against%20broad%20brush%20stereotypes%20on%20both%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706759094000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F31160839%2F278393897_10158302081086965_3013064450962402554_n.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fdid-islam-become-more-syncretic-in-india-an-interview-with-william-dalrymple%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BEvery%20generation%20is%20different%3B%20like%20today%2C%20in%20the%20last%2020%20years%20we've%20seen%20different%20rulers%2C%20each%20with%20different%20views.%20The%20same%20is%20true%20of%20in%20the%2016th%20century%2C%20there%20are%20rulers%20who%20are%20very%20syncretic%20and%20you%20find%20shared%20festivals%20and%20shared%20shrines%2C%20but%20you%20will%20also%20find%20conservatives%20on%20both%20sides%20who%20won't%20mix.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fdid-islam-become-more-syncretic-in-india-an-interview-with-william-dalrymple%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Adidas%20says%20it%20plans%20to%20sell%20remaining%20Yeezy%20sneakers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2