ets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fallout%20of%20the%20story's%20publication%20caused%20irrevocable%20rifts%20between%20Capote%20and%20his%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bswans.%26quot%3B%20According%20to%20Leamer%2C%20the%20excommunication%20that%20followed%20caused%20the%20%26quot%3BIn%20Cold%20Blood%26quot%3B%20author%20to%20sink%20deeper%20into%20a%20dependence%20on%20alcohol%20and%20drugs%2C%20which%20contributed%20to%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.nytimes.com%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Fbooks%2F97%2F12%2F28%2Fhome%2Fcapote-obit.html%3Fmodule%3Dinline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeath%20at%20the%20age%20of%2059%20in%201984%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20wasn't%20the%20only%20untimely%20death%20that%20can%20be%20traced%20back%20to%20the%20publication%20of%20%26quot%3BLa%20C%C3%B4te%20Basque%201965.%26quot%3B%20Ann%20Woodward%2C%20one%20of%20the%20women%20whom%20Capote's%20pen%20appeared%20to%20take%20aim%20at%20in%20the%20Esquire%20story%2C%20died%20by%20suicide%20before%20the%20issue%20hit%20newsstands%2C%20with%20many%20believing%20that%20Capote's%20words%20had%20pushed%20her%20over%20the%20edge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWoodward's%20suicide%20is%20depicted%20in%20the%20first%20episode%20of%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20premiered%20Wednesday%20on%20FX%20and%20Hulu.%20Here's%20the%20real%20story%20of%20what%20happened%20to%20Woodward%20and%20her%20relationship%20with%20Capote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnn%20Woodward%20had%20a%20run%20with%20Truman%20Capote%20where%20she%20reportedly%20called%20him%20a%20homophobic%20slur%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221669%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tom%20Hollander%20protrays%20Truman%20Capote%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65baad217a3d271488765a20%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221252%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETom%20Hollander%20plays%20Truman%20Capote%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EFX%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnn%20Woodward%20(portrayed%20on%20%26quot%3BFeud%26quot%3B%20by%20Demi%20Moore)%20was%20an%20American%20socialite%20whose%20entry%20into%20society%20mirrored%20that%20of%20Capote's%20famed%20%26quot%3BBreakfast%20at%20Tiffany's%26quot%3B%20protagonist%2C%20Holly%20Golightly.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcontent.time.com%2Ftime%2Fsubscriber%2Farticle%2F0%2C33009%2C823933%2C00.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBorn%20Angeline%20Lucille%20Crowell%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20reinvented%20herself%20as%20%26quot%3BAnn%20Eden%26quot%3B%20and%20swapped%20Kansas%20for%20New%20York%20in%20search%20of%20a%20better%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20came%20quickly%2C%20and%20in%201943%2C%20she%20became%20a%20permanent%20fixture%20of%20New%20York%20high%20society%20after%20she%20wed%20wealthy%20banking%20heir%20William%20Woodward%20Jr.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwelve%20years%20later%2C%20in%201955%2C%20she%20became%20something%20of%20a%20permanent%20fixture%20in%20the%20tabloids%2C%20too%2C%20after%20she%20shot%20her%20husband%20at%20their%20Long%20Island%20home.%20His%20death%20was%20ruled%20an%20accident%2C%20and%20Woodward%20faced%20no%20indictment%20after%20she%20alleged%20that%20she%20had%20mistaken%20him%20for%20an%20intruder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20labeled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1999%2F05%2F08%2Fnyregion%2Fheir-fortune-tragedy-suicide-ends-life-wealthy-haunted-man.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Shooting%20of%20the%20Century%26quot%3B%20by%20Life%20magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Woodward%20found%20herself%20cast%20out%20from%20the%20world%20she%20had%20fought%20so%20hard%20to%20enter.%20In%20the%20aftermath%2C%20she%20chose%20to%20leave%20New%20York%20for%20Europe%2C%20according%20to%20a%20biography%20on%20the%20Woodwards%20titled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.goog