%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20known%20exactly%20why%20Capote%20chose%20to%20dramatize%20Woodward's%20killing%20of%20her%20husband%20for%20the%20short%20story%20nearly%20two%20decades%20after%20that%20exchange.%20The%20offense%20he%20took%20from%20her%20insult%20itself%20may%20have%20been%20enough%20ammunition%2C%20but%20Montillo%20speculates%20that%20Capote%20%26quot%3Bloathed%26quot%3B%20Woodward%20because%20%26quot%3Bshe%20reminded%20him%20so%20much%20of%20his%20mother.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20he%20may%20also%20have%20been%20so%20cruel%20to%20her%20because%20Ann%20Woodward%20seemed%20too%20much%20like%20him%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECapote's%20%26quot%3BLa%20C%C3%B4te%20Basque%201965%26quot%3B%20featured%20a%20thinly%20disguised%20character%20based%20on%20Woodward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20%26quot%3BLa%20C%C3%B4te%20Basque%201965%26quot%3B%20was%20published%20in%20November%201975%2C%2020%20years%20had%20passed%20since%20Woodward%20had%20been%20exonerated%20for%20the%20death%20of%20her%20husband.%20But%20the%20story%2C%20which%20sees%20two%20characters%20named%20Lady%20Ina%20Coolbirth%20and%20P.%20B.%20%26quot%3BJonesy%26quot%3B%20Jones%20discuss%20a%20woman%20who%20%26quot%3Bgot%20away%20with%20cold-blooded%20murder%26quot%3B%20when%20she%20killed%20her%20husband%2C%20features%20startlingly%20similar%20circumstances%20to%20the%20Woodward%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Capote's%20story%2C%20Woodward's%20fictional%20stand-in%20is%20named%20Ann%20Hopkins%2C%20and%20her%20husband%20is%20David%20Hopkins.%20The%20two%20women%20discussing%20the%20scandalous%20incident%20are%20also%20widely%20speculated%20to%20be%20based%20on%20Capote's%20close%20confidantes%20Babe%20Paley%20(played%20by%20Naomi%20Watts%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%26quot%3B)%20and%20Nancy%20%26quot%3BSlim%26quot%3B%20Keith%20(played%20by%20Diane%20Lane).%20Both%20women%20also%20fell%20out%20with%20Capote%20over%20the%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWoodward%20was%20found%20dead%20days%20before%20the%20story%20was%20published%20%E2%80%94%20but%20there's%20no%20evidence%20she%20had%20received%20an%20advance%20copy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2010%2C%201975%2C%20a%20few%20days%20before%20the%20issue%20of%20Esquire%20featuring%20%26quot%3BLa%20C%C3%B4te%20Basque%201965%26quot%3B%20was%20published%2C%20Woodward%20was%20found%20dead%20at%20her%20apartment%20on%20Fifth%20Avenue%2C%20having%20consumed%20a%20cyanide%20pill%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vanityfair.com%2Fculture%2F2012%2F12%2Ftruman-capote-answered-prayers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVanity%20Fair.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20evidence%20that%20Woodward%20knew%20the%20excerpt%20would%20mention%20her.%20Still%2C%20it%20has%20been%20heavily%20speculated%20over%20the%20years%20that%20she%20had%20received%20an%20advance%20copy%20of%20the%20story%2C%20which%20influenced%20her%20decision%20to%20take%20her%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223160%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ann%20Woodward's%20thinly-disguised%20character%20in%20Capote's%20story%20was%20called%20Ann%20Hopkins.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bab1d67a3d271488765dc5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223975%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnn%20Woodward's%20thinly-disguised%20character%20in%20Capote's%20story%20was%20called%20Ann%20Hopkins.%3Cp%3EBettmann%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGerald%20Clarke%2C%20Capote's%20biographer%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vanityfair.com%2Fculture%2F2012%2F12%2Ftruman-capote-answered-prayers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVanity%20Fair%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202012%3A%20%26quot%3BWe'll%20never%20know%2C%20but%20it's%20possible%20that%20Truman's%20story%20pushed%20her%20over%20the%20edge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20Braudy's%20book%2C%20Woodward's%20mother-in-law%2C%20Elsie%20Woodward%2C%20was%20among%20those%20who%20believed%20Capote's%20forthcoming%20story%20had%20been%20the%20last%20straw%2C%20stating%20six%20weeks%20after%20her%20suicide%3A%20%26quot%3BShe%20shot%20my%20son%2C%20and%20Truman%20just%20murdered%20her%2C%20and%20so%20now%20I%20suppose%20we%20don't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20that%20anymore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.buzzfeednews.com%2Farticle%2Falessadominguez%2Fdeliberate-cruelty-ann-woodward-murder-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBuzzFeed's%20Alessa%20Dominguez%3C%2Fa%3E%20points%20out%20in%20her%20review%20of%20%26quot%3BDeliberate%20Cruelty%2C%26quot%3B%20other%20factors%2C%20including%20stress%20and%20loneliness%2C%20were%20likely%20plaguing%20Woodward%20in%20her%20final%20weeks%20and%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20two%20decades%20since%20her%20husband's%20death%2C%20Woodward's%20reputation%20was%20still%20in%20tatters%20among%20those%20who%20remembered%20the%20headline-making%20incident.%20Her%20younger%20son%20Jimmy%20had%20tried%20to%20take%20his%20life%20sometime%20before%20her%20death%20too%20(he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Farchives%2Fla-xpm-1999-may-08-mn-35094-story.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edied%20by%20suicide%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20year%20later%2C%20and%20William%2C%20her%20older%20son%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1999%2F05%2F08%2Fnyregion%2Fheir-fortune-tragedy-suicide-ends-life-wealthy-haunted-man.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealso%20died%20the%20same%20way%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201999).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%26quot%3B%20airs%20Wednesdays%20at%2010%20p.m.%20ET%20on%20FX.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffeud-capote-vs-swans-ann-woodward-suicide-death-real-story-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2