The%20government%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ereversed%20the%20country's%20one-child%20policy%20in%202015.%20It%20has%20also%20offered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-one-child-policy-implications-women-children-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20incentives%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20parents%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eall%20the%20while%20extolling%20the%20virtues%20of%20marriage%20and%20childbearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20if%20the%20problem%20lies%20with%20China's%20government%20itself%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWang%20Feng%2C%20a%20sociology%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Irvine%2C%20whose%20research%20areas%20include%20modern%20Chinese%20society%2C%20says%20that%20officials%20have%20known%20for%20a%20long%20time%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-shrinking-population-worker-labor-shortage-grim-omen-global-economy-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edemographic%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20come%20%E2%80%94%20albeit%20not%20as%20quickly%20as%20it%20has%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20the%20regime%20has%20been%20slow%20to%20act%20toward%20a%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Communist%20Party%20officials%20are%20dealing%20with%20the%20consequences%20of%20laws%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-happened-when-people-violated-the-one-child-policy-2015-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone-child%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20to%20the%20outsider%2C%20we%20tend%20to%20think%20that%20these%20regimes%20are%20able%20to%20gather%20national%20resources%20and%20devote%20them%20to%20major%20projects%20and%20can%20delivery%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20Wang%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20adding%20that%20that%20can%20be%20true%20with%20infrastructure%20projects%20such%20as%20China's%20high-speed%20rail.%20%26quot%3BBut%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20policymaking%2C%20it's%20very%20easy%20to%20see%20these%20kind%20of%20regimes%20making%20laws%20that%20are%20disastrous%20and%20are%20very%20slow%20to%20end%20these%20policies%20because%20they%20don't%20really%20want%20to%20take%20on%20the%20political%20baggage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EChina%20pivots%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20Chinese%20Community%20Party%20and%20local%20governments%20have%20shifted%20toward%20laws%20or%20programs%20that%20are%20meant%20to%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eencourage%20young%20women%20to%20bear%20children%20and%20enter%20into%20a%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHangzhou%2C%20a%20populous%20city%20in%20East%20China%2C%20began%20offering%20new%20parents%2020%2C000%20Chinese%20yuan%2C%20or%20about%20%242%2C800%2C%20for%20having%20a%20third%20child.%20In%20Wenzhou%2C%20in%20southeast%20China%2C%20the%20government%20offered%20up%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-cities-hangzhou-subsidies-marriage-leave-boost-birth-rate-population-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3%2C000%20yuan%20per%20child%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20BI's%20Huileng%20Tan%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20ruling%20party%20introduced%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinas-3-child-policy-wont-work-heres-why-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethree-child%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20in%202021%2C%20welcoming%20families%20to%20have%20more%20than%20two%20children.%20But%20still%2C%20the%20Chinese%20population%20%E2%80%94%20young%20people%2C%20in%20particular%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-women-defying-government-pressure-to-rear-more-children-xi-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edid%20not%20bite%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYoung%20people%20are%20laughing%20at%20the%20government%20for%20believing%20that%20it%20actually%20can%20ask%20people%20what%20to%20do%20and%20what%20not%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Wang%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20country's%20one-child%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20solution%20for%20China's%20demographic%20crisis%20likely%20won't%20come%20through%20a%20few%20policy%20initiatives%2C%20Wang%20argued.%20The%20country%20is%20dealing%20with%20a%20deep-rooted%20and%20highly%20complex%20problem%20that%20reflects%20a%20broad%20despair%20and%20pessimism%20young%20people%20have%20about%20their%20future%20as%20the%20country%20has%20gone%20through%20rapid%20economic%20growth%20and%20changes%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20an%20issue%20China%20will%20be%20dealing%20with%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Blong%20haul%2C%26quot%3B%20Wang%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20also%20enacted%20laws%20that%20some%20citizens%20argue%20are%20a%20step%20backward%20from%20its%20efforts%20to%20get%20more%20people%20to%20start%20a%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20government%20implemented%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinas-divorce-rate-dropped-because-of-cooling-off-law-2021-5%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFirst%252C%2520couples%2520are%2520subjected%2520to%2Cfor%2520their%2520official%2520divorce%2520documents.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E30-day%20%26quot%3Bcooling-off%20period%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20married%20couples%20to%20curb%20impulsive%20divorces.%20The%20law%20was%20introduced%2C%20in%20part%2C%20as%20an%20effort%20to%20boost%20the%20country's%20birth%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20online%2C%20some%20Chinese%20citizens%20argue%20that%20it%20discourages%20marriages%2C%20while%20experts%20say%20that%20it%20could%20make%20it%20harder%20for%20women%20to%20get%20out%20of%20abusive%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEthan%20Michelson%2C%20Indiana%20University%20Bloomington's%20department%20chair%20in%20East%20Asian%20Languages%20and%20Cultures%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BDecoupling%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20examines%20divorce%20cases%20in%20China%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20law%20likely%20isn't%20a%20huge%20driver%20in%20the%20country's%20declining%20birth%20or%20marriage%20rates%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20probably%20won't%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20present%20my%20research%20findings%2C%20I%20hear%20this%20all%20the%20time%20from%20Chinese%20women.%20They%20say%2C%20'Why%20on%20earth%20would%20anybody%20get%20married%3F%20Why%20would%20they%20take%20the%20risk%3F'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThere's%20no%20magic%20policy%20wand%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDemocratic%20societies%20have%20also%20experimented%20with%20financial%20incentives%20and%20pro-family%20policies%20yet%20still%20struggle%20with%20birth%20rate%20declines%2C%20Wang%20and%20Michelson%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeoul%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20offered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseoul-giving-parents-1650-cash-vouchers-baby-bonus-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparents%20%241%2C650%20in%20cash%20voucher%3C%2Fa%3Es%20for%20every%20baby%20born%20in%202022.%20In%20Italy%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomans-c-section-italy-free-child-gets-money-from-government-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20giving%20birth%20is%20free%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20country%20offers%20a%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bbaby%20bonus%26quot%3B%20that%20acts%20as%20an%20allowance%20for%20families%20with%20newborns.%20Taiwan%20has%20so%20far%20invested%20%243%20billion%20in%20implementing%20programs%20to%20get%20more%20citizens%20to%20have%20children%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fworld-nation%2Fstory%2F2023-10-24%2Ftaiwan-government-matchmaker-plummeting-birth-rate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Los%20Angeles%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20country%20experienced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F10-countries-at-risk-of-becoming-demographic-time-bombs-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecord-low%20birth%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20within%20the%20past%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bglobal%20shift%2C%26quot%3B%20Wang%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20global%20shift%20in%20what%20it%20means%20to%20have%20a%20family%20and%20the%20meaning%20of%20marriage%20and%20having%20children%20in%20people's%20lives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinas-birth-rate-problem-wont-go-away-with-financial-incentives-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706757357000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b30748f4b446f3be9d28a8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinas-birth-rate-problem-wont-go-away-with-financial-incentives-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22China%20saw%20the%20country's%20demographic%20crisis%20coming.%20The%20government%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20throw%20up%20policies%20that%20can%20fix%20the%20problem%2C%20a%20China%20expert%20says.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lloydlee%40insider.com%20(Lloyd%20Lee)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinas-birth-rate-problem-wont-go-away-with-financial-incentives-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chinese%20hackers%20would%20outnumber%20FBI%20cyber%20agents%20by%2050%20to%201%20even%20if%20the%20agency%20threw%20all%20its%20resources%20at%20China%3A%20FBI%20chief%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22FBI%20chief%20Christopher%20Wray%20(left)%20and%20a%20hacker%20(right).%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bafe5c7a3d271488766e95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BIf%20each%20one%20of%20the%20FBI's%20cyber%20agents%20and%20intelligence%20analysts%20focused%20exclusively%20on%20the%20China%20threat%2C%20China's%20ha