sed%20is%20not%20exactly%20perfect.%20The%20proposed%20Kids%20Online%20Safety%20Act%2C%20or%20KOSA%2C%20would%20give%20parents%20more%20control%20over%20their%20kids'%20accounts%20and%20would%20require%20platforms%20to%20have%20stricter%20privacy%20settings%20for%20teens.%20This%20sounds%20great%2C%20but%20it%20also%20would%20require%20platforms%20to%20prevent%20teens%20from%20accessing%20content%20deemed%20harmful%20to%20teens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrganizations%20like%20the%20ACLU%20and%20the%20Electronic%20Frontier%20Foundation%20oppose%20KOSA%20because%20they%20say%20it%20could%20go%20too%20far.%20For%20example%2C%20it%20could%20be%20interpreted%20to%20require%20platforms%20to%20stop%20kids%20from%20seeing%20content%20about%20trans%20issues%20or%20even%20discussing%20racism.%20(The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dn2H8wx1aBiQ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEFF%20points%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20that%20Sen.%20Marsha%20Blackburn%2C%20Republican%20of%20Tennessee%2C%20one%20of%20the%20bill's%20co-sponsors%2C%20has%20previously%20said%20that%20critical%20race%20theory%20is%20harmful%20to%20kids.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWednesday's%20hearing%20also%20had%20a%20steady%20drumbeat%20of%20wanting%20to%20dismantle%20or%20reform%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-section-230-internet-law-communications-decency-act-explained-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESection%20230%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20rule%20generally%20protects%20internet%20platforms%20from%20being%20liable%20for%20the%20content%20posted%20on%20those%20platforms.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-challenge-section-230-immunity-facebook-google-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESection%20230%20is%20controversial%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20has%20become%20a%20rallying%20point%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-section-230-facebook-trump-clarence-thomas-ajit-pai-2020-10%5C%22%20