d%20on%20a%20GPS%20system%20to%20navigate%20to%20the%20specific%20location%20her%20friend%20had%20sent%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20driver%20shared%20that%20she%20had%20never%20been%20to%20the%20area%20before%20and%20relied%20solely%20on%20the%20GPS%20instructions.%20However%2C%20she%20claimed%20that%20the%20GPS%20guided%20her%20to%20cross%20the%20Wiang%20Thong%20Bridge%2C%20unaware%20of%20any%20restrictions%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20focusing%20on%20the%20GPS%20and%20did%20not%20look%20around.%20I%20thought%20the%20bridge%20was%20sturdy%20and%20likely%20used%20by%20others.%20When%20I%20became%20stuck%2C%20I%20was%20so%20scared%20because%20I%20was%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20Yom%20River.%20I%20was%20afraid%20the%20car%20might%20fall%20into%20the%20river%2C%20so%20I%20got%20out%20of%20the%20car%20to%20seek%20help%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20woman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706723760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2F9g3ghk7g_wiang-thong-bridge_625x300_31_January_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fthai-woman-stranded-on-wooden-bridge-in-hilarious-gps-blunder-4969285%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Thai%20woman%2C%20solely%20relying%20on%20GPS%2C%20got%20her%20car%20stuck%20on%20Wiang%20Thong%20Bridge%2C%20intended%20for%20pedestrians.%20Emergency%20responders%20rescued%20her%20from%20the%20predicament%20witnessed%20by%20a%20passerby.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fthai-woman-stranded-on-wooden-bridge-in-hilarious-gps-blunder-4969285%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fthai-woman-stranded-on-wooden-bridge-in-hilarious-gps-blunder-4969285%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fthai-woman-stranded-on-wooden-bridge-in-hilarious-gps-blunder-4969285%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22HeidelbergCement%20India%20Q3%20results%3A%20Net%20profit%20rises%20to%20Rs%2031.47%20crore%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706723582000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-10%2F28%2Ffull%2F1666978698-0552.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fheidelbergcement-india-q3-results-net-profit-rises-to-rs-31-47-crore-124013101184_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20company%20had%20reported%20a%20net%20profit%20of%20Rs%205.58%20crore%20in%20the%20year-ago%20period%2C%20HeidelbergCement%20India%20said%20in%20a%20regulatory%20filing%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fheidelbergcement-india-q3-results-net-profit-rises-to-rs-31-47-crore-124013101184_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fheidelbergcement-india-q3-results-net-profit-rises-to-rs-31-47-crore-124013101184_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fheidelbergcement-india-q3-results-net-profit-rises-to-rs-31-47-crore-124013101184_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fake%20News%20Or%20Censorship%3F%20Bombay%20High%20Court's%20Split%20Judgment%20On%20IT%20Rules%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20split%20judgement%20on%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20amended%20Information%20Technology%20(IT)%20Rules%20on%20fake%20news%2C%20one%20judge%20of%20the%20Bombay%20High%20Court%20on%20Wednesday%20held%20that%20they%20amounted%20to%20censorship%2C%20while%20the%20other%20judge%20said%20the%20Rules%20do%20not%20have%20any%20chilling%20effect%20on%20free%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20division%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Gautam%20Patel%20and%20Neela%20Gokhale%20delivered%20different%20judgements%2C%20necessitating%20the%20placing%20of%20the%20petitions%20before%20a%20third%20judge.%20Patel%20struck%20down%20the%20Rules%20in%20question%2C%20terming%20them%20as%20unconstitutional%2C%20while%20Gokhale%20dismissed%20the%20petitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20would%20be%20put%20before%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20the%20HC%20to%20be%20assigned%20to%20a%20third%20judge%2C%20the%20division%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20disagreement%20between%20us.%20I%20have%20held%20for%20the%20petitions%20and%20Justice%20Gokhale%20has%20held%20for%20the%20government.%20So%20now%20the%20matter%20will%20be%20heard%20afresh%20by%20a%20third%20judge%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Patel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESolicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20agreed%20to%20extend%20for%20ten%20days%20an%20earlier%20assurance%20that%20until%20the%20judgment%20was%20delivered%2C%20the%20government%20would%20not%20notify%20the%20Fact%20Checking%20Unit%20(FCU)%20to%20be%20set%20up%20under%20the%20Rules%20to%20flag%20fake%20news%20about%20government%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Rules%2C%20if%20the%20FCU%20comes%20across%20or%20is%20informed%20about%20any%20posts%20pertaining%20to%20the%20business%20of%20the%20government%20that%20are%20fake%2C%20false%2C%20and%20contain%20misleading%20facts%2C%20then%20it%20would%20flag%20off%20the%20same%20to%20social%20media%20intermediaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20intermediary%20has%20the%20option%20of%20either%20taking%20down%20the%20post%20or%20putting%20a%20disclaimer%20on%20it.%20In%20the%20second%20option%2C%20the%20intermediary%20loses%20its%20safe%20harbour%2F%20immunity%20and%20stands%20liable%20for%20legal%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPatel%20held%20that%20no%20fundamental%20right%20says%20that%20every%20citizen%20has%20to%20receive%20only%20%26quot%3Btrue%20and%20accurate%20information%20as%20determined%20by%20the%20government%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGokhale%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20held%20the%20right%20to%20share%20fake%20or%20untrue%20information%20was%20not%20part%20of%20the%20free%20speech%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRight%20of%20speech%20will%20not%20enjoy%20protection%20if%20the%20user%20knowingly%20and%20intentionally%20shares%20fake%20or%20misleading%20information%2C%20flagged%20albeit%20by%20a%20FCU...%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPatel%20noted%20that%20the%20FCU%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bthe%20sole%20authority%20to%20decide%20what%20piece%20of%20user-content%20relating%20to%20the%20undefined%20and%20unknowable%20business%20of%20the%20government%20is%20or%20is%20not%20fake.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BHow%20the%20FCU%20will%20go%20about%20its%20business%20is%20also%20unknown....Who%2C%20after%20all%2C%20is%20to%20fact-check%20the%20fact%20checker%3F...Quis%20custodiet%20ipsos%20custodes%20(Who%20will%20guard%20the%20guards)%3F%26quot%3Bhe%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20not%20the%20business%20of%20the%20government%20to%20keep%20citizens%20from%20falling%20into%20error.%20It%20is%20other%20way%20around...it%20is%20very%20much%20business%20and%20should%20be%20the%20duty%20of%20every%20citizen%20to%20prevent%20the%20government%20from%20falling%20into%20error%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20every%20attempt%20to%20whittle%20down%20a%20fundamental%20right%20must%20be%20resisted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Gokhale%20held%20that%20the%20Rules%20were%20not%20violative%20of%20any%20fundamental%20rights%2C%20nor%20did%20they%20suffer%20from%20arbitrariness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Rules%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20encourage%20discussion%20and%20dissemination%20of%20information%20on%20facts%20bereft%20of%20fakery%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20content%20is%20restrained%20by%20the%20impugned%20Rule%2C%20unless%20the%20content%20is%20patently%20false%2C%20untrue%20and%20is%20communicated%20with%20actual%20malice%20that%20is%20with%20knowledge%20of%20its%20falsehood%20and%20with%20reckless%20disregard%20for%20the%20truth%20and%20is%20deceptively%20passed%20off%20as%20a%20statement%20of%20truth%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20right%20to%20free%20expression%20is%20a%20crucial%20and%20indispensable%20component%20of%20a%20nation%20having%20adopted%20democracy.%20However%2C%20this%20right%20does%20not%20permit%20freedom%20to%20share%20information%20which%20a%20person%20knows%20to%20be%20false%20yet%20intentionally%20communicates%20as%20authentic%2C%26quot%3B%20Gokhale%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Patel%20held%20that%20the%20State%20cannot%20coercively%20classify%20speech%20as%20true%20or%20false%20and%20compel%20non-publication%20of%20the%20latter%2C%20as%20this%20was%20nothing%20but%20%26quot%3Bcensorship%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20the%20greatest%20difficulty%20in%20accepting%20the%20proposition%20that%20the%20government%20has%20an%20overriding%20authority%20to%20arrive%20at%20an%20absolutist%20determination%20of%20a%20content%20or%20expression%20as%20the%20truth%2C%20the%20judge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20no%20guidelines%2C%20no%20procedure%20for%20hearing%2C%20no%20opportunity%20to%20counter%20the%20case%20that%20some%20information%20is%20fake%2C%20false%20or%20misleading....%20the%20Rules%20clearly%20make%20the%20Central%20Government%20a%20judge%20in%20its%20own%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGokhale%2C%20however%2C%20noted%20that%20the%20Rules%20provide%20an%20opportunity%20to%20the%20intermediary%20to%20put%20a%20disclaimer%20on%20the%20content%2C%20and%20the%20FCU%20was%20merely%20tasked%20with%20identifying%20information%20concerning%20any%20business%20related%20to%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Rules%20does%20not%20in%20any%20manner%2C%20confer%20any%20authority%20on%20the%20FCU%20to%20direct%20the%20intermediary%20to%20take%20down%20any%20such%20information.%20It%20is%20left%20entirely%20to%20the%20discretion%20of%20the%20intermediary%20to%20make%20reasonable%20effort%20so%20that%20the%20user%20is%20encouraged%20not%20to%20continue%20to%20post%2C%20share%20etc.%20such%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20further%20said%20there%20was%20also%20a%20redressal%20mechanism%20for%20the%20intermediary%20as%20well%20as%20the%20user%2C%20and%20ultimately%20it%20is%20the%20court%20of%20law%20which%20would%20be%20the%20final%20arbiter.%20FCU%20cannot%20be%20presumed%20to%20be%20biased%20only%20because%20the%20power%20to%20notify%20is%20vested%20in%20the%20government%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMembers%20of%20the%20FCU%20would%20be%20those%20who%20are%20privy%20to%20the%20business%20or%20policies%20of%20the%20government%2C%20having%20access%20to%20authentic%20information%20to%20authoritatively%20determine%20any%20information%20as%20fake%2C%20and%20hence%20the%20FCU%20cannot%20be%20termed%20as%20biased%2C%20Justice%20Gokhale%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPatel%20noted%20that%20one%20fully%20government-controlled%20entity%2C%20Press%20Information%20Bureau%2C%20is%20active%20and%20already%20has%20significant%20social%20media%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20sinister%20and%20insidious%20facet%20to%20the%20impugned%20amendment%20is%20that%20this%20new%20agency%20(FCU)%20has%20far%20more%20than%20a%20loud%20bark%3A%20it%20has%20fangs%20and%20claws%2C%20for%20its%20unilateral%20view%20of%20what%20is%20or%20is%20not%20the%20'truth'%20is%20accompanied%20by%20a%20requirement%20of%20removal%20of%20what%20is%20has%20so%20determined%20(to%20be%20fake%2C%20false%20or%20misleading)%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStand-up%20comedian%20Kunal%20Kamra%2C%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%2C%20and%20Association%20of%20Indian%20Magazines%20filed%20petitions%20in%20the%20HC%20against%20the%20Rules%2C%20terming%20them%20arbitrary%20and%20unconstitutional%20and%20claiming%20that%20they%20would%20have%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20April%206%2C%202023%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20promulgated%20amendments%20to%20the%20Information%20Technology%20(Intermediary%20Guidelines%20and%20Digital%20Media%20Ethics%20Code)%20Rules%2C%202021%2C%20including%20a%20provision%20for%20a%20fact-checking%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706723520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2Fcourt-generic_625x300_1527245477936.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffake-news-or-censorship-bombay-high-courts-split-judgment-on-it-rules-4968678%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20split%20judgement%20on%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20amended%20Information%20Technology%20(IT)%20Rules%20on%20fake%20news%2C%20one%20judge%20of%20the%20Bombay%20High%20Court%20on%20Wednesday%20held%20that%20they%20amounted%20to%20censorship.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffake-news-or-censorship-bombay-high-courts-split-judgment-on-it-rules-4968678%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffake-news-or-censorship-bombay-high-courts-split-judgment-on-it-rules-4968678%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffake-news-or-censorship-bombay-high-courts-split-judgment-on-it-rules-4968678%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Day%20Before%20Retiring%2C%20Varanasi%20Judge%20Hands%20Over%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20Basement%20to%20Hindus%20For%20Worship%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F23142008%2FGyan-vapi-mosque-min.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20district%20judge%20in%20Varanasi%20on%20Wednesday%20(January%2031)%20%E2%80%93%20his%20last%20working%20day%20before%20retirement%20%E2%80%93%20allowed%20Hindus%20to%20worship%20inside%20a%20sealed%20basement%20of%20the%20the%20Mughal-era%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20in%20a%20decision%20that%20could%20have%20far-reaching%20consequences%20in%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid-Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Temple%20legal%20matter%20that%20is%20being%20heard%20in%20courts%20at%20all%20three%20levels%20of%20the%20judiciary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Hindu%20priests%20and%20Hindu%20devotees%20visiting%20the%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Temple%20would%20also%20get%20access%20to%20visit%20and%20perform%20%3Cem%3Epuja%3C%2Fem%3E%20inside%20the%20%3Cem%3Etehkhana%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20the%20mosque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hindu%20plaintiffs%2C%20who%20are%20seeking%20religious%20rights%20within%20the%20mosque%20as%20well%20as%20its%20ultimate%20possession%20from%20Muslims%2C%20dubbed%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20as%20a%20victory%20and%20equated%20it%20to%20the%20controversial%20unlocking%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%201986.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Babri%20Masjid%20was%20eventually%20demolished%20by%20a%20mob%20of%20Hindu%20activists%20assembled%20at%20the%20call%20of%20members%20of%20the%20Sangh%20%3Cem%3Eparivar%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20December%206%2C%201992.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20caretakers%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20were%20stunned%20by%20the%20district%20court%20order%20and%20said%20the%20court%20accepted%20claims%20made%20by%20the%20temple%20side%20without%20seeking%20any%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Varanasi%20court%20order%20comes%20days%20after%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India%20(ASI)%20in%20its%20survey%20report%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fasis-survey-report-says-a-large-hindu-temple-existed-under-the-gyanvapi-mosque%5C%22%3Eclaimed%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Clarge%20Hindu%20temple%E2%80%9D%20existed%20there%3C%2Fa%3E%20prior%20to%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20existing%20structure%20%E2%80%93%20i.e.%2C%20the%20mosque%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%20parts%20of%20the%20temple%20were%20modified%20and%20used%20in%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Islamic%20place%20of%20worship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDistrict%20judge%20Ajaya%20Krishna%20Vishvesha%20directed%20the%20district%20administration%20to%20make%20arrangements%20for%20puja%20and%20other%20Hindu%20activities%20inside%20the%20southern%20tehkhana%2C%20or%20cellar%2C%20of%20the%20mosque%20within%20seven%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudge%20Vishvesha%20directed%20the%20administration%20to%20conduct%20the%20puja%20and%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Erag-bhog%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cidols%E2%80%9D%20inside%20the%20tehkhana%20through%20a%20priest%20appointed%20by%20the%20Shri%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Temple%20Trust%2C%20which%20manages%20the%20adjoining%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Mandir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20passed%20the%20order%20on%20an%20application%20filed%20by%20local%20priest%20Shailendra%20Kumar%20Pathak%20of%20the%20Acharya%20Ved%20Vyas%20Peeth%20temple%2C%20who%20had%20sought%20rights%20to%20worship%20the%20Maa%20Shringar%20Gauri%20and%20other%20alleged%20visible%20and%20invisible%20deities%20he%20claimed%20were%20in%20the%20cellar%20of%20the%20mosque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20caretakers%20of%20the%20mosque%20rejected%20all%20claims%20made%20by%20Pathak%20that%20there%20were%20idols%20kept%20inside%20the%20previously%20sealed%20cellar%20and%20that%20his%20ancestors%20used%20to%20carry%20out%20puja%20inside%20the%20cellar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudge%20Vishvesha%2C%20however%2C%20ruled%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Hindu%20plaintiff%20and%20directed%20the%20district%20administration%20to%20make%20the%20necessary%20iron%20fencing%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20puja.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20district%20magistrate%20had%20on%20January%2024%20completed%20the%20process%20of%20taking%20over%20the%20cellar%20after%20the%20court%20on%20January%2017%20directed%20the%20district%20magistrate%20to%20keep%20the%20cellar%20secure%20and%20appointed%20him%20as%20its%20receiver.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20application%2C%20Pathak%20claimed%20that%20there%20were%20idols%20kept%20in%20the%20southern%20cellar%20of%20the%20mosque%20and%20that%20his%20ancestors%20as%20priests%20conducted%20worship%20of%20the%20idols%20kept%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Pathak%20further%20claimed%20that%20%E2%80%9CPujari%20Vyas%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20or%20Somnath%20Vyas%2C%20his%20maternal%20grandfather%2C%20was%20prevented%20from%20entering%20the%20barricaded%20area%20of%20the%20mosque%20after%20December%201993.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rag-bhog%20and%20%3Cem%3Esanskar%3C%2Fem%3E%20rituals%20were%20also%20stopped%2C%20Pathak%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20claimed%20that%20ancient%20Hindu%20idols%20and%20several%20other%20religious%20items%20linked%20to%20the%20Hindu%20religion%20were%20inside%20the%20cellar.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20necessary%20to%20carry%20out%20regular%20puja%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Emurtis%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5Bidols%5D%20inside%20the%20tehkhana%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20management%20committee%20of%20the%20Anjuman%20Intezamia%20Masajid%2C%20which%20manages%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%2C%20vehemently%20denied%20the%20claims%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20in%20written%20applications%20told%20the%20court%20that%20no%20member%20of%20the%20Vyas%20family%20ever%20carried%20out%20puja%20in%20the%20cellar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20the%20question%20of%20stopping%20someone%20from%20conducting%20puja%20from%20December%201993%20does%20not%20arise%2C%20the%20committee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNo%20alleged%20idol%20was%20ever%20present%20at%20the%20site%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20committee%20said%20and%20denied%20Pathak%E2%80%99s%20claims%20that%20his%20family%20had%20ancestral%20occupation%20of%20the%20cellar.%20The%20cellar%20has%20always%20been%20under%20the%20occupation%20of%20the%20mosque%20committee%2C%20the%20caretakers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVishnu%20Shankar%20Jain%2C%20one%20of%20the%20lawyers%20for%20the%20temple%20side%20in%20the%20matter%2C%20hailed%20the%20court%20order%20as%20historic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDistrict%20court%20Varanasi%20has%20created%20history%20today%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jain%20tweeted%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20to%20reporters%2C%20he%20said%20this%20was%20the%20first%20step%20for%20Hindus%20towards%20gaining%20ownership%20of%20the%20mosque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CJustice%20K.M%20Pandey%20during%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20movement%20ordered%20the%20opening%20of%20the%20locks%20%5Bof%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%5D%20on%20February%201%2C%201986.%20I%20see%20this%20order%20in%20a%20similar%20vein.%20This%20is%20the%20turning%20point%20in%20this%20case.%20It%20is%20a%20historic%20order%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jain%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ES.M.%20Yasin%2C%20joint%20secretary%20of%20the%20masjid%20committee%2C%20was%20dismayed%20by%20the%20court%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNow%20we%20have%20no%20hope%20of%20justice%20in%20this%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20Yasin%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYasin%20rejected%20the%20claims%20made%20by%20the%20temple%20side%20and%20said%20that%20no%20puja%20had%20ever%20been%20held%20in%20the%20tehkhana%20and%20that%20there%20are%20no%20idols%20there.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20only%20bamboo%20poles%20there.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20are%20all%20lies.%20They%20have%20no%20evidence.%20The%20court%20passed%20the%20order%20without%20any%20evidence%2C%E2%80%9D%20Yasin%20continued%20to%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20questioned%20why%20the%20judge%20did%20not%20seek%20a%20factual%20position%20from%20the%20district%20administration%2C%20which%20had%20sealed%20the%20cellar%20and%20barricaded%20the%20premises%20in%201995%20on%20the%20directions%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20cellar%20has%20always%20been%20in%20our%20possession%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Yasin%2C%20who%20objected%20to%20the%20breach%20of%20the%20old%20barricade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lawyers%20of%20the%20mosque%20side%20also%20said%20that%20the%20Deen%20Mohammad%20suit%20of%201937%20did%20not%20make%20any%20mention%20of%20a%20Vyas%20family%20occupying%20the%20tehkhana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnion%20Minister%20Giriraj%20Singh%2C%20commenting%20on%20the%20development%2C%20said%20that%20just%20two%20cellars%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20had%20been%20opened%20and%20the%20others%20were%20still%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEarlier%20too%2C%20Hindus%20offered%20puja%20there.%20But%20it%20was%20later%20prevented.%20The%20court%20has%20not%20given%20something%20new%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESamajwadi%20Party%20chief%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20posted%20on%20X%3A%20%E2%80%9CDue%20process%20has%20to%20be%20maintained%20while%20following%20any%20court%20order.%20The%20Varanasi%20Court%20fixed%20a%207%20day%20period%20for%20it.%20What%20we%20are%20seeing%20now%20is%20a%20concerted%20effort%20to%20go%20beyond%20the%20due%20process%20and%20prevent%20any%20legal%20recourse%20that%20can%20be%20taken.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20hearing%20is%20on%20February%208%2C%20by%20when%20the%20mosque%20side%20can%20file%20their%20objections.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706722745000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F23142008%2FGyan-vapi-mosque-min.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fjudge-hands-over-gyanvapi-basement-to-hindus%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20passed%20the%20order%20on%20an%20application%20filed%20by%20local%20priest%20who%20sought%20rights%20to%20worship%20the%20Maa%20Shringar%20Gauri%20and%20other%20alleged%20visible%20and%20invisible%20deities%20he%20claimed%20were%20in%20the%20mosque's%20cellar.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22eng