%20the%20hackles%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20whilst%20potentially%20disturbing%20politicians%20of%20all%20political%20parties%2C%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20foremost%20electronic%20voting%20machine%20(EVM)%20experts%20has%20said%20that%20while%20EVMs%20cannot%20be%20hacked%2C%20because%20they%20are%20not%20connected%20to%20Wi-Fi%2C%20Bluetooth%20or%20the%20Internet%2C%20they%20can%20be%20easily%20manipulated.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMadhav%20Deshpande%2C%20a%20former%20CEO%20of%20Tulip%20Software%20and%20a%20former%20consultant%20to%20the%20Obama%20administration%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20has%20also%20said%20that%20the%20remedy%20to%20guard%20against%20this%20manipulation%20is%20simple%2C%20straightforward%20and%20inexpensive.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20Deshpande%20has%20both%20identified%20the%20problem%20and%20provided%20the%20solution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2037-minute%20interview%20to%20Karan%20Thapar%2C%20Madhav%20Deshpande%20began%20by%20explaining%20that%20EVMs%2C%20which%20comprise%20three%20separate%20units%2C%20i.e.%20the%20ballot%20unit%2C%20the%20control%20unit%20and%20the%20voter-verified%20paper%20audit%20trail%20(VVPAT)%20machine%2C%20are%20%E2%80%9Cunder-designed%E2%80%9D%2C%20by%20which%20he%20meant%20that%20they%20are%20relying%20on%20an%20old%20technology%20which%20has%20considerably%20advanced%20since%20it%20was%20first%20used%20for%20EVMs%20but%20those%20advances%20have%20not%20been%20incorporated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20there%20are%20holes%20and%20gaps%20in%20the%20system%20which%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20permit%20tampering%20to%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20interview%2C%20Deshpande%20goes%20on%20to%20discuss%20two%20ways%20in%20which%20the%20voting%20can%20be%20manipulated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20is%20to%20do%20with%20the%20VVPAT%20machine%20and%20the%20way%20the%20present%20configuration%20of%20the%20three%20voting%20machines%20places%20the%20VVPAT%20between%20the%20ballot%20unit%20and%20the%20control%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20will%20leave%20you%20to%20see%20the%20interview%20to%20understand%20and%20follow%20Deshpande%E2%80%99s%20argument%20as%20well%20as%20to%20hear%20and%20understand%20his%20remedy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20way%20voting%20can%20be%20manipulated%20is%20through%20the%20control%20unit.%20Because%20any%20control%20unit%20can%20work%20with%20any%20ballot%20unit%2C%20it%20is%20theoretically%20possible%20to%20change%20the%20control%20unit%20after%20the%20voting%20has%20happened%20or%20to%20pre-load%20it%20with%20manufactured%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20the%20solution%20is%20simple%20and%20straightforward.%20It%20requires%20effective%20pairing%20through%20a%20serial%20cable.%20And%2C%20once%20again%2C%20I%20will%20leave%20you%20to%20see%20the%20interview%20to%20find%20out%20further%20details%20about%20this%20potential%20problem%20as%20well%20as%20the%20remedy%20Deshpande%20suggests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20point%20Deshpande%20makes%20is%20the%20need%20for%20geolocation%20tracking%20with%20a%20GPS%20attachment%20to%20ensure%20that%20EVMs%20do%20not%20go%20astray%20or%20can%20be%20traced%20and%20recovered%20if%20they%20fall%20into%20wrong%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20ensure%20the%20geolocation%20tracking%20does%20not%20lead%20to%20the%20EVM%20becoming%20hackable%2C%20Deshpande%20says%20it%20must%20not%20be%20electronically%20connected%20to%20the%20EVMs%2C%20but%20simply%20attached.%20Again%2C%20I%20will%20leave%20you%20to%20hear%20the%20interview%20to%20find%20out%20greater%20details%20of%20Deshpande%E2%80%99s%20suggestion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20very%20important%20interview%20because%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20an%20EVM%20expert%20has%20shown%20how%20EVMs%20can%20be%20manipulated%20%E2%80%93%20but%20not%20hacked%20%E2%80%93%20and%20how%20we%20can%20easily%20and%20simply%20guard%20against%20this%20manipulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20we%20%E2%80%9Cknow%E2%80%9D%20EVMs%20can%20be%20manipulated%2C%20if%20action%20is%20not%20taken%20to%20immediately%20remedy%20and%20rectify%20this%20fear%2C%20concern%20that%20manipulation%20is%20happening%20could%20proliferate.%20It%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20incumbent%20on%20the%20Election%20Commission%20to%20act%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20elections%20just%20over%20two%20months%20away%2C%20this%20is%20a%20very%20important%20interview%20which%20you%20should%20see%20for%20yourself.%20I%20have%20deliberately%20not%20paraphrased%20what%20Deshpande%20has%20said%20but%20only%20given%20you%20the%20broad%20main%20points.%20You%20should%20see%20and%20hear%20this%20interview%20for%20yourself.%20Deshpande%20has%20spoken%20simply%2C%20clearly%20and%20without%20technical%20jargon%20so%20you%20should%20have%20no%20problem%20following%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fz5Y6z29El3I%3Fsi%3DbYLCtk_UCk_7alln%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706709644000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F31184826%2FKT-31B.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fevms-can-be-manipulated-not-hacked-madhav-deshpande%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Madhav%20Deshpande%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20to%20%E2%80%98The%20Wire%E2%80%99%20that%20because%20EVMs%20rely%20on%20older%20technology%20that%20has%20since%20considerably%20advanced%2C%20there%20are%20holes%20and%20gaps%20in%20the%20system%20which%20permit%20tampering%20to%20happen.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fevms-can-be-manipulated-not-hacked-madhav-deshpande%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22You%20Can't%20Use%20Paytm%20Wallet%2C%20Transfers%20After%20Feb%2029.%20See%20Banned%20Services%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20has%20taken%20action%20against%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%20after%20it%20directed%20the%20bank%20to%20not%20onboard%20new%20customers%20over%20supervisory%20concerns.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20RBI%20directed%20the%20bank%20to%20appoint%20an%20Income%20Tax%20audit%20firm%20to%20conduct%20a%20comprehensive%20System%20Audit%20of%20its%20IT%20system%20over%20non-compliance%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20move%20by%20the%20RBI%20comes%20after%20the%20Comprehensive%20System%20Audit%20report%20and%20subsequent%20compliance%20validation%20report%20of%20the%20external%20auditors%20revealed%20persistent%20non-compliance%20and%20warranted%20further%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20RBI%20has%20exercised%20its%20powers%20under%20the%20Banking%20Regulation%20Act%20and%20has%20stopped%20the%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%20from%20offering%20some%20services%20to%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENo%20further%20deposits%2C%20credit%20transactions%20or%20top-ups%20will%20be%20allowed%20in%20any%20customer%20accounts%2C%20prepaid%20instruments%2C%20wallets%2C%20FASTags%2C%20or%20National%20Common%20Mobility%20Cards%20after%20February%2029.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECustomers%20can%20utilise%20the%20money%20in%20their%20account%20for%20withdrawal%2C%20but%20no%20further%20deposits%20are%20allowed.%20The%20customers%20can%20utilise%20the%20existing%20amount%20in%20their%20FASTags%2C%20wallets%2C%20savings%20accounts%2C%20current%20accounts%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20bank%20cannot%20provide%20services%20like%20fund%20transfers%2C%20irrespective%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20service%2C%20which%20will%20not%20be%20allowed%20after%20February%2029.%20The%20customers%C2%A0will%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20use%20the%20UPI%20facility%20of%20the%20bank%20either.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20nodal%20accounts%20of%20One97%20Communications%20Ltd%2C%20the%20parent%20company%20of%20Paytm%2C%20and%20the%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%20have%20been%20terminated%20by%20the%20RBI.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFor%20transactions%20initiated%20on%20or%20before%20February%2029%2C%20all%20settlements%20have%20to%20be%20concluded%20by%20March%2015%2C%20and%20no%20further%20transactions%20are%20permitted.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706709360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-09%2Fpaytm-payments-bank_650x400_51505220288.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fyou-cant-use-paytm-wallet-transfers-after-feb-29-see-affected-features-4967286%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20has%20taken%20action%20against%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%20after%20it%20directed%20the%20bank%20to%20not%20onboard%20new%20customers%20over%20supervisory%20concerns.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fyou-cant-use-paytm-wallet-transfers-after-feb-29-see-affected-features-4967286%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fyou-cant-use-paytm-wallet-transfers-after-feb-29-see-affected-features-4967286%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fyou-cant-use-paytm-wallet-transfers-after-feb-29-see-affected-features-4967286%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BCanada's%20Politics%20Gave%20Space%20To%20Separatism%2C%20Extremism%26quot%3B%3A%20S%20Jaishankar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ECanada%20ignored%20India's%20request%20for%20sharing%20information%20about%20any%20concerns%20they%20may%20have%2C%20and%20instead%20made%20allegations%20in%20public%20against%20India%20over%20the%20killing%20of%20Khalistani%20terrorist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%20in%20June%202023%2C%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20told%20NDTV%20in%20an%20interview%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECanada's%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20had%20kicked%20up%20a%20massive%20diplomatic%20row%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20over%20the%20murder%20of%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%2C%20which%20Mr%20Trudeau%20said%20was%20allegedly%20shot%20dead%20by%20%26quot%3BIndian%20government%20agents%26quot%3B%20outside%20a%20gurdwara%20in%20Surrey%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20faulted%20the%20condition%20of%20Canada's%20politics%20in%20which%20extremist%20elements%20have%20got%20themselves%20embedded%2C%20as%20the%20major%20factor%20behind%20Canada's%20recent%20behaviour%20towards%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCanada%2C%20for%20some%20years%2C%20has%20been%20giving%20space%20to%20extremists%20and%20terrorists%20in%20their%20politics.%20I%20believe%20this%20is%20a%20weakness%20in%20their%20politics.%20A%20lot%20of%20problems%20have%20happened%20there%20because%20of%20this.%20It%20should%20not%20have%20happened%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheir%20Prime%20Minister%20made%20an%20allegation%20against%20us%20in%20public.%20Before%20that%2C%20both%20Prime%20Ministers%20met%2C%20and%20I%20was%20also%20there.%20Our%20position%20then%20was%20that%20if%20there%20is%20anything%20in%20your%20mind%20that's%20worrying%20you%2C%20any%20information%20you%20got%2C%20please%20tell%20us.%20Even%20if%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20tell%20us%20everything%2C%20at%20least%20say%20something%2C%20so%20that%20we%20can%20investigate%20from%20our%20side%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20did%20not%20share%20anything%2C%20but%20made%20allegations%20in%20public.%20In%20comparison%2C%20see%20the%20example%20of%20the%20US.%20The%20US%20told%20us%20that%20they%20have%20some%20information%20about%20criminals%2C%20and%20they%20will%20give%20us%20some%20information%20to%20look%20into%20from%20our%20side%2C%20and%20we%20will%20compare%20the%20information%2C%20investigate%20the%20matter%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Eternal%20Affairs%20Minister%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSeparatism%2C%20extremism%2C%20and%20violence%20have%20been%20given%20space%20in%20Canada's%20politics.%20There%20is%20no%20such%20problem%20in%20the%20US.%20Yes%2C%20they%20have%20other%20issues%2C%20but%20there%20is%20a%20difference%20between%20Canada%20and%20the%20US%20in%20their%20politics%2C%20their%20approach%2C%20and%20how%20they%20handle%20bilateral%20relationships%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20row%20over%20an%20alleged%20plot%20to%20murder%20US-based%20Khalistani%20terrorist%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20rejected%20Mr%20Trudeau's%20allegation%20as%20%26quot%3Babsurd%26quot%3B.%20Canada%20shared%20no%20specific%20information%20regarding%20its%20charges%2C%20India%20had%20said%2C%20flagging%20%26quot%3Bpolitically%20condoned%20hate%20crimes%20and%20criminal%20violence%26quot%3B%20in%20that%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706708280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fi7v75mpg_s-jaishankar-ndtv-650_650x400_31_January_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcanadas-politics-gave-space-to-separatism-extremism-s-jaishankar-4967625%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Canada%20ignored%20India's%20request%20for%20sharing%20information%20about%20any%20concerns%20they%20may%20have%2C%20and%20instead%20made%20allegations%20in%20public%20against%20India%20over%20the%20killing%20of%20Khalistani%20terrorist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%20in%20June%202023%2C%20S%20Jaishankar%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcanadas-politics-gave-space-to-separatism-extremism-s-jaishankar-4967625%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcanadas-politics-gave-space-to-separatism-extremism-s-jaishankar-4967625%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcanadas-politics-gave-space-to-separatism-extremism-s-jaishankar-4967625%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Global%20Corruption%20Index%202023%3A%20India%20Ranks%2093rd%20Out%20of%20180%20Countries%2C%20Was%2085th%20in%202022%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F10%2Fdown-with-corruption_Flickr.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20%3Cspan%3EAn%20annual%20global%20index%20on%20corruption%20for%202023%20has%20placed%20India%20at%20a%20much%20worse%20position%20than%20it%20was%20a%20year%20ago.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20index%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Union%20government%20run%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20is%20targeting%20only%20opposition%20leaders%20through%20its%20investigating%20agencies%20%E2%80%93%20ostensibly%20to%20weaken%20their%20public%20appeal%20before%20the%20crucial%202024%20general%20elections%20and%20project%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20as%20corrupt.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESignificantly%2C%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%2028%20states%2C%20BJP%20and%20its%20allies%20were%20in%20power%20in%2017%20in%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20the%20country-wise%20corruption%20perception%20index%20(CPI)%20of%20the%20report%20put%20together%20by%20Transparency%20International%20(TI)%2C%20a%20noted%20platform%20that%20works%20in%20over%20a%20hundred%20countries%20to%20fight%20corruption%20and%20promote%20transparency%20in%20public%20life%2C%20India%20has%20slipped%20from%2085%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20position%20in%202022%20to%2093rd%20in%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20all%2C%20TI%20ranks%20180%20countries%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20perceived%20levels%20of%20public%20sector%20corruption%20in%20a%20scale%20of%200%20to%20100%3B%20the%20perceived%20levels%20are%20drawn%20from%20consultations%20with%20experts%20and%20people%20in%20business%20in%20the%20respective%20countries.%20Those%20closer%20to%20the%20scale%20of%20100%20are%20perceived%20to%20be%20highly%20corrupt.%20While%20India%20stands%20at%2093%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20overall%20score%20for%202023%20stands%20at%2039%2C%20one%20point%20lower%20than%202022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transparency.org%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fcpi-2023-asia-pacific-stagnation-due-to-inadequate-anti-corruption-commitments%5C%22%3EAbout%20India%2C%20the%20TI%20report%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20(39)%20shows%20score%20fluctuations%20small%20enough%20that%20no%20firm%20conclusions%20can%20be%20drawn%20on%20any%20significant%20change.%20However%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20elections%2C%20India%20sees%20further%20narrowing%20of%20civic%20space%2C%20including%20through%20the%20passage%20of%20a%20bill%20that%20could%20be%20a%20%E2%80%98grave%20threat%20to%20fundamental%20rights%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20neighbours%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmong%20India%E2%80%99s%20neighbours%2C%20China%20is%20shown%20at%20a%20score%20of%2042%20(against%20India%E2%80%99s%2039)%20but%20the%20report%20cautions%20that%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20heavy%20reliance%20on%20punishment%20rather%20than%20institutional%20checks%20on%20power%20raises%20doubts%20over%20the%20long-term%20effectiveness%E2%80%9D%20of%20its%20anti-corruption%20measures.%20China%2C%20which%20has%20been%20grabbing%20headlines%20for%20cracking%20down%20on%20corruption%2C%20has%20punished%20over%203.7%20million%20public%20officials%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20shows%20Bangladesh%20at%20a%20dismal%20score%20of%2024%2C%20stating%20that%20%E2%80%9Cflow%20of%20information%20on%20the%20public%20sector%20is%20hindered%20amidst%20an%20ongoing%20crackdown%20against%20the%20(domestic)%20Press%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMyanmar%20under%20the%20Junta%20rule%2C%20is%20at%20a%20low%20score%20of%2020.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20TI%20report%2C%20while%20placing%20Pakistan%20and%20Sri%20Lanka%20in%2029%20and%2034%20respectively%2C%20has%20underlined%20that%20these%20two%20countries%20are%20wrestling%20with%20their%20respective%20weak%20financial%20situations%20and%20political%20instability%20but%20they%20also%20%E2%80%9Chave%20strong%20judicial%20oversight%20which%20is%20helping%20to%20keep%20the%20government%20in%20check.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20Pakistan%20strengthened%20citizens%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20information%20by%20expanding%20this%20right%20under%20Article%2019A%20of%20its%20constitution%20to%20previously%20restricted%20institutions.%20In%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20found%20that%20the%20former%20president%2C%20prime%20minister%20and%20other%20officials%20were%20responsible%20for%20the%202021%20economic%20crisis%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20highlighted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmong%20the%20ASEAN%20countries%2C%20Malaysia%20is%20placed%20at%2050%20which%20is%20%E2%80%9Cabove%20the%20regional%20average%E2%80%9D%20because%20of%20its%20%E2%80%9Crobust%20elections%20alongside%20an%20anti-corruption%20commission%20that%20has%20delivered%20on%20high-profile%20cases%20over%20the%20last%20decade.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHighlighting%20the%20point%20that%20its%20global%20corruption%20barometer%20had%20revealed%20the%20prevalence%20of%20corruption%20around%20election%20processes%20in%20Asia%20and%20Pacific%20regions%2C%20the%20report%20also%20stated%20that%20its%202020%20survey%20in%20Asia%20showed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cnearly%20one%20in%20seven%20people%20had%20been%20offered%20bribes%20in%20exchange%20for%20votes%20in%20a%20national%2C%20regional%20or%20local%20election%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmong%20Asian%20countries%2C%20where%20corruption%20is%20well%20fought%20are%20in%20Singapore%20(83)%2C%20Hong%20Kong%20(75)%2C%20Japan%20(73)%2C%20Bhutan%20(68)%2C%20Taiwan%20(67)%20and%20South%20Korea%20(63).%20Among%20the%20countries%20globally%20to%20have%20impressive%20scores%20in%20terms%20of%20controlling%20corruption%20are%20New%20Zealand%20(85)%20and%20Australia%20(75).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20silent%20BJP%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20ruling%20party%20is%20silent%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20slipping%20position%20in%20the%20global%20corruption%20index%20put%20out%20by%20TI%2C%20the%20party%20was%20seen%20making%20a%20noise%20back%20in%202014%20with%20some%20of%20its%20leaders%20accusing%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20of%20wrongly%20taking%20credit%20for%20having%20fought%20corruption%20successfully%20by%20its%20government%20in%20Delhi%20by%20citing%20a%20TI%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJournalist-turned-politician%20Shazia%20Ilmi%2C%20then%20with%20AAP%2C%20had%20claimed%20in%20public%20that%20corruption%20in%20Delhi%20had%20abated%20considerably%20following%20the%20party%20coming%20to%20power%2C%20citing%20a%20%E2%80%9Csurvey%E2%80%9D%20passed%20on%20to%20her%20by%20a%20person%20who%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20former%20employee%20of%20the%20Transparency%20International.%20The%20same%20%E2%80%98survey%E2%80%99%20was%20quoted%20by%20Delhi%20chief%20minister%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20at%20a%C2%A0%20meeting%20organised%20by%20the%20Confederation%20of%20Indian%20Industries%20(CII)%2C%20leading%20TI%20to%20issue%20a%20media%20statement%20that%20it%20had%20wound%20up%20its%20office%20in%20India%20and%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20that%20%E2%80%98survey%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAAP%20soon%20issued%20a%20clarification%20and%20apologised%20to%20TI%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20any%20embarrassment%20that%20this%20controversy%20may%20have%20caused%20to%20the%20organisation%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EResponding%20to%20the%20issue%2C%20among%20others%2C%20Delhi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Faap-issues-clarification-on-transparency-international-regrets-error-on-corruption-report%2Farticleshow%2F30610915.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3EBJP%20leader%20Harsh%20Vardhan%20had%20told%20reporters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CAAP%20and%20Kejriwal%20are%20both%20liars.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20TI%20has%20no%20India%20chapter%2C%20there%20exists%20a%20Delhi-based%20organisation%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftransparencyindia.org%2Four-founder%2F%5C%22%3ETransparency%20International%20%E2%80%93%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20founded%20by%20S.D.%20Sharma%2C%20a%20Gandhian.%20Sharma%20was%20also%20a%20part%20of%20the%20campaign%20against%20corruption%20in%202011%20which%20ultimately%20led%20to%20the%20birth%20of%20AAP%20as%20a%20political%20party.%20However%2C%20he%20later%20walked%20out%20of%20the%20campaign%20over%20differences%20with%20activist%20Anna%20Hazare.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706707846000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F10%2Fdown-with-corruption_Flickr.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fglobal-corruption-index-2023-india-ranks-93rd-out-of-180-countries-was-85th-in-2022%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'...%5BA%5Dhead%20of%20the%20elections%2C%20India%20sees%20further%20narrowing%20of%20civic%20space%2C'%20the%20report%20says.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fglobal-corruption-index-2023-india-ranks-93rd-out-of-180-countries-was-85th-in-2022%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BTies%20With%20Neighbours%20Not%20Transactional%26quot%3B%3A%20S%20Jaishankar%20On%20Foreign%20Policy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndia's%20relationships%20with%20its%20immediate%20neighbours%20is%20not%20of%20a%20transactional%20nature%2C%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20told%20NDTV%20Wednesday%20evening.%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20pointed%20out%20it%20was%20New%20Delhi%20that%20started%20the%20'Neighbourhood%20First'%20policy%20and%20had%20forged%20friendships%20based%20on%20this%20sentiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSri%20Lanka%20is%20an%20example%20of%20the%20neighbourhood%20policy...%20the%20world%20talked%20about%20Sri%20Lanka%20but%20India%20helped...%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20told%20NDTV%2C%20recalling%20the%20weeks%20of%20economic%20and%20social%20crises%20that%20plagued%20the%20island%20nation%20in%20May%202022%2C%20sparking%20violence%20that%20claimed%20lives%20and%20made%20headlines%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20more%20startling%20visuals%20was%20protesters%20barging%20into%20and%20capturing%20then-President%20Gotabaya%20Rajapaksa's%20Colombo%20residence%2C%20forcing%20security%20personnel%20to%20fire%20shots%20in%20the%20air%20to%20hold%20back%20a%20mob%20of%20literally%20hundreds%20while%20the%20Sri%20Lankan%20leader%20was%20escorted%20to%20safety%20by%20the%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20disturbing%20visuals%20were%20of%20large-scale%20arson%20and%20rioting%2C%20and%20of%20hundreds%20of%20people%20queuing%20up%20for%20essential%20goods%20like%20petrol%20or%20diesel%2C%20food%2C%20and%20life-saving%20medicines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESri%20Lanka%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20international%20community%20for%20help%20and%20did%20receive%20some%20support%2C%20particularly%20from%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20which%20released%20a%20%242.9%20billion%20package.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20was%20India%20that%20acted%20first%20and%20most%20decisively%2C%20providing%20nearly%20%244%20billion%20in%20food%20and%20financial%20assistance%2C%20as%20well%20as%20shipments%20of%20fuel%2C%20medicines%2C%20and%20urea%20(fertilisers)%20for%20the%20next%20sowing%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20aid%20to%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20highlighted%2C%20was%20not%20contingent%20on%20any%20reciprocity%20or%20'favour'%20to%20be%20performed%20at%20a%20later%20date.%20It%20was%20simply%20an%20effort%20to%20help%20a%20struggling%20neighbour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20speed%20of%20that%20aid%20was%20commended%20by%20the%20United%20States%20Agency%20for%20International%20Development%2C%20or%20USAID%2C%20which%20is%20an%20independent%20agency%20of%20the%20US%20government.%20USAID%20said%20India%20had%20acted%20%26quot%3Breally%20swiftly%26quot%3B%20to%20help%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20but%20calls%20to%20Beijing%20to%20provide%20relief%20had%20gone%20unanswered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20agency%20had%20also%20said%20China%20had%20become%20one%20of%20Sri%20Lanka's%20biggest%20creditors%2C%20%26quot%3Boften%20offering%20opaque%20loan%20deals%20at%20higher%20interest%20rates%20than%20other%20lenders%26quot%3B%20to%20finance%20%26quot%3Bheadline-grabbing%20infrastructure%20projects%20with%20often%20questionable%20practical%20use%20for%20Sri%20Lankans...%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20referred%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bmassive%20port%20that%20has%20generated%20little%20income...%26quot%3B%20-%20seen%20as%20a%20note%20on%20the%20Hambantota%20Port%2C%20which%20has%20been%20taken%20over%20by%20the%20Chinese%20and%20has%20hosted%20Beijing's%20spy%20ships.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20also%20referred%20to%20improved%20ties%20in%20the%20Gulf%20region%2C%20which%20he%20called%20India's%20%26quot%3Bextended%20neighbourhood%26quot%3B%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BOur%20ties%20with%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20have%20improved%20by%20leaps%20in%2010%20years%20(of%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%20last%20year%20the%20Union%20Minister%20had%20also%20spoken%20about%20India%20providing%20Covid%20vaccines%20to%20neighbourhood%20countries%20in%20need%2C%20such%20as%20Afghanistan%20and%20Myanmar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20message%20I%20have%20is%20that%20this%20is%20a%20time%20for%20India%20to%20step%20up%20its%20support%20to%20its%20neighbours...%20to%20look%20at%20each%2C%20sit%20with%20them%2C%20and%20understand%20what%20their%20problems%20are%20and%20see%20what%20we%20can%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20time%20for%20us%20to%20demonstrate%20that%20neighbourhood%20first%20really%20delivers.%20Not%20just%20in%20terms%20of%20lines%20of%20credit%20but%20also%20in%20terms%20of%20investments.%20If%20Indian%20tourists%20go%20out%2C%20if%20Indian%20businesses%20go%20out%2C%20also%20if%20Indian%20government's%20investments%20can%20shore%20up%20other%20people's%20economy%20and%20expand%20employment...and%20I%20can%20assure%20them%20that%20India%20will%20rise%20to%20that%20occasion%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706707740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Frhc5a98s_s-jaishankar-interview_625x300_31_January_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fties-with-neighbours-not-transactional-s-jaishankar-on-foreign-policy-4967534%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India's%20relationships%20with%20its%20immediate%20neighbours%20is%20not%20of%20a%20transactional%20nature%2C%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20told%20NDTV%20Wednesday%20evening.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fties-with-neighbours-not-transactional-s-jaishankar-on-foreign-policy-4967534%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fties-with-neighbours-n